2 HOUSE BILL 769
1 Annotated Code of Maryland
2 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
3 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
4 Article – Health Occupations
5 Section 19–309.1 19–101(e)
6 Annotated Code of Maryland
7 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
8 BY adding to
9 Article – Health Occupations
10 Section 19–101(o–1) and 19–309.2
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – Health Occupations
16 19–101.
17 (a) In this title the following words have the meanings indicated.
18 (c–1) “Conditional license” means a license issued by the Board under, and as
19 limited by, § 19–309.1 of this title to practice:
20 (1) Bachelor social work; or
21 (2) Master social work.
22 (e) “License” means, unless the context requires otherwise:
23 (1) One of four categories of licenses issued by the Board authorizing an
24 individual to practice:
25 (i) Bachelor social work;
26 (ii) Master social work;
27 (iii) Certified social work; or
28 (iv) Certified social work–clinical; or
29 (2) A conditional license issued by the Board; OR
30 (3) A PROVISIONAL LICENSE ISSUED BY THE BOARD.

HOUSE BILL 769 3
1 (O–1) “PROVISIONAL LICENSE” MEANS A LICENSE ISSUED BY THE BOARD
2 UNDER, AND AS LIMITED BY, § 19–309.2 OF THIS TITLE TO PRACTICE:
3 (1) BACHELOR SOCIAL WORK; OR
4 (2) MASTER SOCIAL WORK.
5 19–309.2.
6 (A) BEGINNING NOVEMBER 1, 2026, THE BOARD SHALL ISSUE A
7 PROVISIONAL LICENSE TO AN APPLICANT WHO, EXCEPT FOR PASSING THE
8 EXAMINATION OTHERWISE REQUIRED UNDER THIS SUBTITLE, HAS MET THE
9 APPROPRIATE EDUCATION AND EXPERIENCE REQUIREMENTS OF THIS SUBTITLE
10 FOR A LICENSE ISSUED UNDER § 19–302 OF THIS SUBTITLE TO PRACTICE:
11 (1) BACHELOR SOCIAL WORK; OR
12 (2) MASTER SOCIAL WORK.
13 (B) A PROVISIONAL LICENSE:
14 (1) AUTHORIZES THE HOLDER TO PRACTICE SOCIAL WORK IN THE
15 STATE ONLY WITHIN THE SCOPE OF THE SPECIFIC CATEGORY OF LICENSE ISSUED
16 BY THE BOARD;
17 (2) REQUIRES THE HOLDER TO PRACTICE UNDER THE SUPERVISION
18 OF A BOARD–APPROVED SUPERVISOR IN ACCORDANCE WITH REGULATIONS
19 ADOPTED UNDER THIS SECTION;
20 (3) MAY BE ISSUED ONLY TO AN INITIAL APPLICANT FOR LICENSURE
21 WHO HAS NOT PREVIOUSLY BEEN LICENSED UNDER THIS TITLE; AND
22 (4) DOES NOT QUALIFY THE HOLDER FOR A MULTISTATE LICENSE
23 UNDER THE SOCIAL WORK LICENSURE COMPACT ESTABLISHED UNDER § 19–3A–01
24 OF THIS TITLE.
25 (C) A PROVISIONAL LICENSE:
26 (1) EXPIRES ON A DATE SET BY THE BOARD THAT IS AT LEAST 12
27 MONTHS, BUT NOT MORE THAN 24 MONTHS, AFTER THE DATE OF ISSUANCE;
28 (2) MAY NOT BE RENEWED FOR AN ADDITIONAL TERM NOT
29 EXCEEDING 24 MONTHS; AND

4 HOUSE BILL 769
1 (3) SHALL TERMINATE AUTOMATICALLY ON:
2 (I) THE EXPIRATION DATE; OR
3 (II) IF THE HOLDER APPLIES AND QUALIFIES FOR A LICENSE
4 UNDER SUBSECTION (E) OF THIS SECTION, THE DATE THAT THE FULL LICENSE IS
5 ISSUED.
6 (D) A HOLDER OF A PROVISIONAL LICENSE AND THE SUPERVISING SOCIAL
7 WORKER ARE JOINTLY RESPONSIBLE FOR ENSURING COMPLIANCE WITH THE
8 SUPERVISION AND EXPIRATION REQUIREMENTS OF SUBSECTIONS (B)(2) AND (C) OF
9 THIS SECTION.
10 (E) THE BOARD SHALL ISSUE A FULL LICENSE UNDER § 19–302 OF THIS
11 SUBTITLE TO A HOLDER OF A PROVISIONAL LICENSE WHO DEMONSTRATES TO THE
12 SATISFACTION OF THE BOARD THAT THE HOLDER HAS ACHIEVED A SATISFACTORY
13 SCORE ON AN EXAMINATION, AS REQUIRED UNDER § 19–302 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
14 (F) SUPERVISED HOURS COMPLETED UNDER A PROVISIONAL LICENSE:
15 (1) MAY BE COUNTED TOWARD THE SUPERVISED EXPERIENCE
16 REQUIRED FOR INDEPENDENT PRACTICE APPROVAL UNDER § 19–302(F) OF THIS
17 SUBTITLE; AND
18 (2) MAY BE COUNTED TOWARD THE SUPERVISED EXPERIENCE
19 REQUIRED TO QUALIFY FOR A CERTIFIED SOCIAL WORKER–CLINICAL LICENSE
20 UNDER § 19–302(E) OF THIS SUBTITLE.
21 (G) THE BOARD SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS TO CARRY OUT THIS SECTION,
22 INCLUDING REGULATIONS THAT ESTABLISH:
23 (1) MINIMUM SUPERVISION REQUIREMENTS AND REPORTING
24 PROCEDURES;
25 (2) STANDARDS FOR EVALUATING SUPERVISED PRACTICE AS
26 DESCRIBED IN SUBSECTION (E)(2) OF THIS SECTION;
27 (3) REQUIREMENTS TO ENSURE THAT THE TRACKING OF
28 PROVISIONAL LICENSES ALIGNS WITH EXISTING LICENSURE CYCLES; AND
29 (4) A REASONABLE FEE FOR THE ISSUANCE OF A PROVISIONAL
30 LICENSE SUFFICIENT TO COVER ADMINISTRATIVE COSTS.

HOUSE BILL 769 5
1 (H) ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 31 EACH YEAR, BEGINNING IN 2027, THE
2 BOARD SHALL REPORT TO THE SENATE FINANCE COMMITTEE AND THE HOUSE
3 HEALTH COMMITTEE, IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT
4 ARTICLE, THE FOLLOWING INFORMATION FOR THE IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING
5 12–MONTH PERIOD:
6 (1) THE TOTAL NUMBER OF ACTIVE LICENSEES WHO WERE LICENSED
7 WITHOUT PASSING THE EXAMINATION REQUIRED UNDER THIS SUBTITLE AND THE
8 AVERAGE NUMBER OF YEARS THOSE LICENSEES HAVE PRACTICED IN THE STATE;
9 (2) (1) THE NUMBER OF PROVISIONAL LICENSES ISSUED;
10 (3) (2) THE NUMBER OF HOLDERS OF PROVISIONAL LICENSES WHO
11 OBTAINED FULL LICENSURE UNDER SUBSECTION (E) OF THIS SECTION; AND
12 (4) (3) ANY RECOMMENDATIONS FOR IMPROVING:
13 (I) THE IMPLEMENTATION OF THIS SECTION; AND
14 (II) THE IMPACT OF THIS SECTION ON THE HEALTH CARE
15 WORKFORCE.
16 19–309.1.
17 (a) [If an administrative delay for any reason or an unforeseen circumstance, act,
18 or occurrence prevents an examination required under this subtitle from being available to
19 an applicant for a period of at least 15 business days, the] THE Board [may] SHALL issue
20 a conditional license to an applicant who, except for passing the examination OTHERWISE
21 REQUIRED UNDER THIS SUBTITLE, has met the appropriate education and experience
22 requirements of this subtitle for a license issued under § 19–302 of this subtitle to practice:
23 (1) Bachelor social work; or
24 (2) Master social work.
25 (b) A conditional license issued under this section [authorizes]:
26 (1) AUTHORIZES the holder to practice social work in the State only
27 WITHIN THE SCOPE OF THE SPECIFIC CATEGORY OF LICENSE ISSUED BY THE BOARD;
28 (2) REQUIRES THE HOLDER TO PRACTICE under the supervision of a
29 Board–approved supervisor [while the conditional license is effective] IN ACCORDANCE
30 WITH REGULATIONS ADOPTED UNDER THIS SECTION; AND

6 HOUSE BILL 769
1 (3) MAY BE ISSUED ONLY TO AN INITIAL APPLICANT FOR LICENSURE
2 WHO HAS NOT PREVIOUSLY BEEN LICENSED UNDER THIS TITLE.
3 (c) A conditional license [is valid until 180 days after the examination becomes
4 readily available to the applicant]:
5 (1) EXPIRES ON A DATE SET BY THE BOARD THAT IS AT LEAST 12
6 MONTHS, BUT NOT MORE THAN 24 MONTHS, AFTER THE DATE OF ISSUANCE;
7 (2) MAY NOT BE RENEWED; AND
8 (3) SHALL TERMINATE AUTOMATICALLY ON:
9 (I) THE EXPIRATION DATE; OR
10 (II) IF THE HOLDER APPLIES AND QUALIFIES FOR A LICENSE
11 UNDER SUBSECTION (E) OF THIS SECTION, THE DATE THAT THE FULL LICENSE IS
12 ISSUED.
13 (D) A HOLDER OF A CONDITIONAL LICENSE UNDER THIS SECTION AND THE
14 SUPERVISING SOCIAL WORKER ARE JOINTLY RESPONSIBLE FOR ENSURING
15 COMPLIANCE WITH THE SUPERVISION AND EXPIRATION REQUIREMENTS OF
16 SUBSECTIONS (B)(2) AND (C) OF THIS SECTION.
17 (E) THE BOARD SHALL ISSUE A FULL LICENSE UNDER § 19–302 OF THIS
18 SUBTITLE TO A HOLDER OF A CONDITIONAL LICENSE UNDER THIS SECTION WHO
19 DEMONSTRATES TO THE SATISFACTION OF THE BOARD THAT THE HOLDER HAS:
20 (1) ACHIEVED A SATISFACTORY SCORE ON AN EXAMINATION, AS
21 REQUIRED UNDER § 19–302 OF THIS SUBTITLE; OR
22 (2) COMPLETED AT LEAST 1,500 HOURS OF SUPERVISED
23 EXPERIENCE IN THE PRACTICE OF SOCIAL WORK DURING THE PERIOD OF
24 CONDITIONAL LICENSURE, AS VERIFIED BY A BOARD–APPROVED SUPERVISOR, IN
25 ACCORDANCE WITH STANDARDS ESTABLISHED BY THE BOARD, IN CONSULTATION
26 WITH AN INSTITUTION THAT:
27 (I) IS ACCREDITED BY THE COUNCIL ON SOCIAL WORK
28 EDUCATION OR AN EQUIVALENT ORGANIZATION APPROVED BY THE COUNCIL ON
29 SOCIAL WORK EDUCATION; AND
30 (II) OFFERS BOTH A BACCALAUREATE DEGREE AND A MASTER’S
31 DEGREE.

HOUSE BILL 769 7
1 (F) THE BOARD SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS TO CARRY OUT THIS SECTION,
2 INCLUDING REGULATIONS THAT ESTABLISH:
3 (1) MINIMUM SUPERVISION REQUIREMENTS AND REPORTING
4 PROCEDURES;
5 (2) STANDARDS FOR EVALUATING SUPERVISED PRACTICE AS
6 DESCRIBED IN SUBSECTION (E)(2) OF THIS SECTION;
7 (3) REQUIREMENTS TO ENSURE THAT THE TRACKING OF
8 CONDITIONAL LICENSES ISSUED UNDER THIS SECTION ALIGNS WITH EXISTING
9 LICENSURE CYCLES; AND
10 (4) A REASONABLE FEE FOR THE ISSUANCE OF A CONDITIONAL
11 LICENSE ISSUED UNDER THIS SECTION SUFFICIENT TO COVER ADMINISTRATIVE
12 COSTS.
13 [(d)] (G) On or before December 31 each year, beginning in [2024,] 2026, the
14 Board shall report to the Senate Finance Committee and the House Health and
15 Government Operations Committee, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government
16 Article, the following information for the immediately preceding 12–month period:
17 [(1) Whether the examination was unavailable at any time during the
18 reporting period; and
19 (2) If the examination was unavailable:
20 (i) The number of applicants who were eligible for a conditional
21 license due to the unavailability of the examination;
22 (ii) The number of applicants who applied to take the examination;
23 (iii) The number of applications that were delayed in processing; and
24 (iv) The number of conditional licenses issued under this section.]
25 (1) THE NUMBER OF CONDITIONAL LICENSES ISSUED UNDER THIS
26 SECTION;
27 (2) THE NUMBER OF HOLDERS OF CONDITIONAL LICENSES WHO
28 OBTAINED FULL LICENSURE UNDER SUBSECTION (E) OF THIS SECTION; AND
29 (3) ANY RECOMMENDATIONS FOR IMPROVING:

8 HOUSE BILL 769
1 (I) THE IMPLEMENTATION OF THIS SECTION; AND
2 (II) THE IMPACT OF THIS SECTION ON THE HEALTH CARE
3 WORKFORCE.
4 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act is an emergency
5 measure, is necessary for the immediate preservation of the public health or safety, has
6 been passed by a yea and nay vote supported by three–fifths of all the members elected to
7 each of the two Houses of the General Assembly, and shall take effect from the date it is
8 enacted.
Approved:
